It's about `forms`.

I found out that the `Validators.required` function adds the `required` attribute to the html input element. But I cannot find any related code. I just found the validator it self. But I guess that there is some code what checks if exactly **this** validator is set and binds the required attribute to it. But how to register an own custom required validator?

https://github.com/angular/angular/blob/0abb67af59a92a2b29082a259aa9f4ea3fbaab7d/packages/forms/src/validators.ts#L209-L211

I'm currently working on a custom required validator this an conditional callback function. Btw. it would be great if Angular provides an build-in validator for this by extending this validator like: 

```ts
this.form = new FormGroup({
  name: new FormControl(null, { validators: Validators.required(() => this.isNameRequired()) })
})

// this.isNameRequired checks other form controls like a checkbox and returns true on checked state.
// One known issue: The validator is not updated on form changes. We need to update and validate method manually.
```

This is either an feature to add an conditional required validator or to allow custom required validators with automatic required attribute on the input element. I also wonder where the magic happens (in code). It's no question for StackOverflow. ...

The current alternative is to subscribe to valueChange and change validators, which is a bit ugly way to do that.

